## Schema Markup for AI Citation

Structured data helps AI systems understand and extract Dermadry content. Implement these schemas:

### Priority schemas for Dermadry:

| Page Type | Schema Types | Why |
|-----------|-------------|-----|
| Product pages | `MedicalDevice`, `Product`, `FAQPage` | Device details, pricing, Q&A extraction |
| Blog/condition pages | `Article`, `MedicalWebPage`, `FAQPage` | Author, date, topic identification |
| How-to/treatment pages | `HowTo`, `FAQPage` | Step extraction for process queries |
| About/company page | `Organization`, `MedicalBusiness` | Entity recognition by AI |
| Review/testimonial pages | `Review`, `AggregateRating` | Trust signals |

### FAQPage Schema (highest AI citation impact):

```json
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is iontophoresis?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Iontophoresis is a non-invasive treatment that uses mild electrical currents to reduce excessive sweating. According to a study published in the Journal of the American Academy of Dermatology, iontophoresis is effective for treating palmar, plantar, and axillary hyperhidrosis."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is the Dermadry device FDA-cleared?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Dermadry is an FDA-cleared Class II medical device for the treatment of hyperhidrosis (excessive sweating) of the hands, feet, and underarms."
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### MedicalDevice Schema:

```json
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "MedicalDevice",
  "name": "Dermadry Total",
  "manufacturer": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Dermadry Laboratories Inc.",
    "url": "https://www.dermadry.com"
  },
  "relevantSpecialty": "Dermatology",
  "medicalSpecialty": "Dermatology",
  "indication": "Treatment of hyperhidrosis (excessive sweating) of the hands, feet, and underarms",
  "description": "FDA-cleared iontophoresis device for at-home treatment of hyperhidrosis"
}
```

